<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="2" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[192,1440,641,762]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,328,641,665]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. This small (
<quantity box="[489,582,642,666]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" unit="mm" value="2.4">2.4 mm</quantity>
long) species is immediately recognized by the pair of frontal carinae being strong, distant from the eyes, each arcing toward the meson and becoming approximate between the eyes, and then diverging anterolaterally. A ventral incision of each compound eye is broadly triangular and extends approximately to the center of each eye.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[192,1440,801,890]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,484,801,825]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Specimens examined</emphasis>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[499,644,802,826]" name="Bahamas" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">BAHAMAS</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion box="[656,744,802,826]" country="Bahamas" name="South Andros" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Andros</collectingRegion>
Is., Forfar Field Sta., nr Stafford Creek, 
<date box="[1256,1435,801,825]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" value="2006-07-22" valueMax="2006-07-28" valueMin="2006-07-22">22-28-vii-2006</date>
, MC Thomas, TRSmith, UV trap in coastal coppice (1, FSCA). The 
<typeStatus box="[1012,1117,834,858]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">holotype</typeStatus>
was examined along with high-resolution images (
<bibRefCitation author="MCZ Type Database" box="[489,815,866,890]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" refId="ref3422" refString="MCZ Type Database 2014. https: // insects. oeb. harvard. edu / mcz (accessed 12 October 2014)." type="url" year="2014">MCZ Type Database 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[192,1441,929,1050]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,271,930,954]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Notes</emphasis>
. This is the “ 
<taxonomicName box="[441,696,930,954]" class="Insecta" family="Throscidae" genus="Aulonothroscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undefined-1">
<emphasis box="[441,631,930,954]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Aulonothroscus</emphasis>
sp. 1
</taxonomicName>
” of 
<bibRefCitation author="Turnbow, R. H., Jr. &amp; M. C. Thomas" box="[751,1116,930,954]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" pagination="1 - 64" refId="ref3673" refString="Turnbow, R. H., Jr., and M. C. Thomas 2008. An annotated checklist of the Coleoptera (Insecta) of the Bahamas. Insecta Mundi 0034: 1 - 64." type="book chapter" year="2008">Turnbow and Thomas (2008)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Horn, G. H." box="[1128,1278,929,953]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" pagination="198 - 208" refId="ref3185" refString="Horn, G. H. 1885. Synopsis of the Throscidae of the United States. Transactions of the American Entomological Society 12: 198 - 208." type="journal article" year="1885">Horn (1885)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Horn" baseAuthorityYear="1885" class="Insecta" family="Throscidae" genus="Aulonothroscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="convergens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">A. convergens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Georgia. 
<bibRefCitation author="Blanchard, E." box="[501,714,962,986]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" pagination="1 - 26" refId="ref2965" refString="Blanchard, E. 1917. Revision of the Throscidae of North America (Coleoptera). Transactions of the American Entomological Society 43: 1 - 26." type="journal article" year="1917">Blanchard (1917)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Leng, C. W." box="[723,870,962,986]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" refId="ref3357" refString="Leng, C. W. 1920. Catalogue of the Coleoptera of America, north of Mexico. John D. Sherman, Jr.; Mount Vernon, New York. 470 p." type="book" year="1920">Leng (1920)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Kirk, V. M." box="[931,1069,961,986]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" refId="ref3322" refString="Kirk, V. M. 1969. A list of beetles of South Carolina, Part 1 - Northern Coastal Plain. South Carolina Agricultural Experiment Station Technical Bulletin 1033. 124 p." type="book" year="1969">Kirk (1969)</bibRefCitation>
listed the species from District of Columbia, Georgia, Florida, Louisiana, North Carolina, New York, South Carolina, and Tennessee. This report of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Horn" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[367,534,1026,1049]" class="Insecta" family="Throscidae" genus="Aulonothroscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="convergens">
<emphasis box="[367,534,1026,1049]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">A. convergens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[607,778,1026,1050]" name="Bahamas" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">The Bahamas</collectingCountry>
provides a 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[919,1193,1026,1050]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">new country record</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
